x guofeng cao amy wilson andy warhol art in america banksy christies contemporary art curator deborah freedman digital cprint editioned artwork etching exclusive gagosian gallery hub culture ida applebroog ifpda interviews irving penn jasper johns joan winter john baldessari judy pfaff kenny scharf lithograph lithography metropolitan museum of art moma museum of modern art pablo picasso photography printmaking prints rostarr tate modern the metropolitan museum of art the museum of modern art the new york times the school of visual arts the whitney museum of american art video whitney museum whitney museum of american art about editionedart making art accessible to all an often underestimated art genre fine art limited editions belong to a world of its own our curators and art experts bring unparalleled connoisseurship of the field and shed new light on the most important issues facing printmaking and photography today join their intelligent discussions share your opinions on collecting and art management peak inside studios and private art collections and more be sure to browse our curated selection of editionedartcom for new editions and artist exclusives questions or comments infoeditionedartcom resources aperture foundation christie’s center for contemporary printmaking independent curators international international center of photography philagrafika print fair the american print alliance international fine print dealers association ifpda newsletter enter email for the latest news  updates submit care to contribute seeking magazine contributors we accept articles covering the print and photography worlds in particular we are looking for art reviews market coverage collection visits event coverage and notable achievements email us at infoeditionedartcom home multimedia artist bios contributors shop contact  editionedart  all rights reserved  website custom designed  powered by ppweb technologies michael ray charles  artnet my account log in  artnet log in home auctions artists galleries auction houses events news michael ray charles american born  artworks biography auction results dealers events filter sort × biography michael ray charles is a contemporary american painter his work explores historic african american stereotypes from the antebellum south appropriating images from advertising and pop culture to expose the underlying racism prevalent in contemporary culture charles creates a mimetic vocabulary of cultural racial and historicized images to subvert those themes and explore surviving caricatures that continue to appear in popular media such as aunt jemima or sambo “stereotypes have evolved i’m trying to deal with present and past stereotypes in the context of today’s society” the artist has said born in lafayette la in  he went on to earn his bfa from mcneese state university and his mfa from the university of houston his work has been both critically celebrated and the source of controversy and in  charles was the subject of an art short documentary he was appointed as the hugh roy and lillie cranz cullen distinguished professor of painting in  at the university of houstons school of art and he has exhibited internationally notably in the austin museum of art the knox art gallery and the museum of modern art in new york related categories african american art contemporary art related artists jeanmichel basquiat elmer simms campbell norman lewis gordon parks kara walker artworks for sale object type paintings  × prints and multiples  × period s  × galleries  × michael ray charles  results recently added artwork title a to z artwork title z to a artwork date ascending artwork date descending load more back to top michael ray charles black cats go off  gallery schlesinger price on request michael ray charles liberty bros permanent daily circus the  galerie vintage price on request michael ray charles forever free the greatest show on earth  tony shafrazi gallery price on request michael ray charles forever free b